[32m│[0m ### thoughts                                                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The reconnaissance was highly successful. The application was                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m comprehensively mapped through manual browsing and directory brute-forcing   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m (using dirb). The critical vulnerability is clearly an IDOR issue in the     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m cookie-based authentication system, which is a common but severe security    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m flaw. The serialized PHP object in the cookie is trusted by the server       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m without server-side validation, allowing trivial privilege escalation. The   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m flag was successfully retrieved by manipulating the userid parameter to      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m access the administrative account (userid=1). This represents a complete     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m compromise of the application's access control mechanism.                    [32m│[0m
